description:
Ireland is enforcing a domestic travel restrictions. From 15 September 2020 people should:
- Stay at home;
- Exercise within 5 kilometres of home;
- There will be a penalty for movement outside 5 kilometres of home, with the following exemptions;
- Travel to and from work, where work involves providing an essential service 
- To attend medical appointments and collect medicines and other health products for vital family reasons, such as providing care to children, elderly or vulnerable people, and in particular for those who live alone but excluding social family visits 
- For farming purposes, that is food production or care of animals
- To visit a grave
